article.headline: Morehead State 70, Tennessee-Martin 48
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Junior guard Brandon Callahan came off the bench to score a career high 22 points as Morehead State defeated Tennessee-Martin 70-48 Saturday afternoon. Callahan scored 17 of his 22 in the second half when Morehead State hit 15 of 22 from the field, including 6 of 10 3-pointers. The Skyhawks (5-14, 3-6 Ohio Valley Conference) never led, but stayed close and trailed only 29-23 at the half. Morehead State pushed the lead to 44-32 early in the second half, but saw Tennessee-Martin reel off eight straight to get within 44-40. The Eagles (10-6, 6-2 OVC) finished the game on a 26-8 run to secure the win. Callahan hit 7 of 8 from the field, including 4 of 5 3-pointers and 4 of 4 from the free throw line. Quentin Pryor also finished in double figures for Morehead State with 11. Tennessee-Martin had only one double digit scorer as Cleve Woodfork had 15. Morehead State's bench outscored the Skyhawks 38-16.
